cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper involves the development of a mobile phone-based participatory sensing system for tourists to collect subjective data about sightseeing spots. The system uses filtering rules generated by Interactive Growing Hierarchical SOM and C4.5 algorithms to provide important information to users. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.SD) techniques. Finally, the paper also involves the study of cybernetics (cs.CY) as it deals with the interaction between humans and technology.
